						               													<description>Donostiarrok harriz harri is a cooperative game about the reconstruction of Donostia / San Sebastian after its burning in 1813 by Wellington troops. &amp;#10;The players, representing witnesses of the massacre and inhabitants of the city - Juana Francisca Arsuaga (servant), Jos&amp;eacute; Antonio Aguirrebarrena (carpenter), Mar&amp;iacute;a D. Miloy &amp;quot;La naipera&amp;quot;, Vda. de Barbot (maker of cards) and Manuel Joaqu&amp;iacute;n de Alcain Baraibar (merchant and mayor) must rebuild the city, they all win or lose together.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;gameplay:&amp;#10;The board represents the burned intramural city, with a grid of paths that the characters must travel. &amp;#10;At start of game the four characters are in the Plaza Nueva among the remains of the city.&amp;#10;The 4 players must rebuild the city. For that they must help each other to figure out where to start the reconstruction and to get the seven parts of the facade of a typical reconstruction building.&amp;#10;To advance, some brick tiles are used and as many bricks as the number of steps you want to advance will be used. &amp;#10;But the reconstruction was not easy and that is why the game also has adversity events (discouragement, illnesses, wars, lack of money).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
